--- Answer (gateway_degradation) ---
## Finding: stripe-proxy is failing at ~10-16x the rate of every other gateway right now

Looking at the last 3 minutes (3,148 total transactions across 4 gateways):

| Gateway | Failure rate | Volume |
|---|---|---|
| **stripe-proxy** | **42.8%** | 810 txns |
| braintree-edge | 4.6% | 763 txns |
| checkout-io | 3.5% | 791 txns |
| adyen-gw | 2.7% | 784 txns |

Stripe-proxy's failure rate (0.4284) is roughly 9x braintree-edge, 12x checkout-io, and 16x adyen-gw — well outside normal variance given the other three cluster tightly between 2.7-4.6%.

This is not a fresh spike — checking the last 60 minutes for stripe-proxy alone shows a nearly identical 43.85% failure rate (837 total events), so this has been sustained, not a sudden blip in the last 3 minutes.

**What's failing:** A semantic search of stripe-proxy failures in this window shows a mix of standard card decline reasons rather than one single error signature — e.g. transaction `ebf1112d-2b8a-4e46-9e8d-b5e42377c71f` ("51: INSUFFICIENT FUNDS"), `f5f44bc5-500b-4944-9ea2-eca19b8bbc5c` and `1bf18471-a8bd-4420-a387-ce3c1dfb56fd` ("Declined - insufficient funds available"), `7bb1d6fe-aa2a-4570-8199-b735abc809c2` ("ERR_82 invalid CVC"), and `6e03ef96-6550-470d-ad3e-c5a5caa985c3` ("Declined - do not honor"). The variety of decline reasons suggests this isn't a single upstream outage signature but an elevated overall decline rate specific to this gateway — worth checking against stripe-proxy's own upstream/processor status.

Data currency: I did not check freshness on this specific query — if timing precision matters, I can run `system_freshness` to confirm ingest lag.


